modules.description: Provides functions for compressing and decompressing data using the BZ2 algorithm, including `compress` and `decompress` operations. Works with byte sequences and input/output channels for efficient data handling. Used to reduce file sizes for storage or transmission and to restore original data from compressed streams.

Provides functions for reading from and writing to BZ2-compressed streams, including opening, reading, writing, and closing channels. Works with in_channel and out_channel types, as well as byte arrays for data manipulation. Used to decompress data from a file stream and compress raw byte sequences into BZ2 format.
